NAME

  **ls** - output contents of directory


SYNOPSIS

    ls 

DESCRIPTION

    Ls (short for list) outputs the contents of the current directory. Each 
    file or directory within the current will be outputted on a new line. 
    For each file, the permissions will be displayed first, followed by the
    file/directory name. Passing any arguments will cause ls to return an
    error.

SEE ALSO

    chmod, file, pwd